full_text:
I have to second what Frank mentioned.  The EVP Maker/allophones combo is excellent, in my opinion.  I know a lot of folks do not like it, but I find it utterly fascinating.  It is an animal all it&#39;s own so I can&#39;t really compare it to radio sweep, however, I do recommend people trying it to see if it might be a good match for them.  I&#39;ve been working with it since Stefan created the allophones file and have been consistently amazed at the results.  

Of all methods I&#39;ve tried, I have the most success with &quot;real-time, two-way&quot; communication via this combination.  It took some getting used to, hearing the relevant parts while ignoring the rest, but once I got the hang of that it become more and more easy as I worked with it.

Frank, it&#39;s great to read there&#39;s a possibility of some inexpensive FB&#39;s coming along.  Very cool.

Margaret  

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Sumption &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  There should be cheap FBs available soon, if the rumors I hear are
&gt; correct.  I have printed circuit boards made, but the troubel is---no tuner!
&gt; I don&#39;t want to have to rely on the Radio Shack models--that they
&gt; discontinued, and so far home made tuners are just too noisy(staticy).
&gt; 
&gt;  In the mean time, like Margaret said, many of the oterh method work as
&gt; well, and sometimes better. There&#39;s also EVPmaker.
