&gt; &gt; Hi Susan. I don&#39;t know what kind of box you&#39;ll end up with, but in the
&gt; &gt; meantime, you can always do &quot;manual radio sweep.&quot; I get some of my best
&gt; &gt; results that way. When I started doing sweep for EVP, commercially available
&gt; &gt; boxes were not available. My favorite unit so far is the Duracell KP028
&gt; &gt; crank flashlight/radio. It might be listed as the &quot;3 in 1&quot; or something like
&gt; &gt; that. The knob is just the right size and tightness to make it easy to sweep
&gt; &gt; from one end to the other. Of course, it&#39;s a little obnoxious to have to
&gt; &gt; stop and crank it up every few minutes, but I think the results make it well
&gt; &gt; worth the effort. I&#39;ve seen others have good success with all kinds of
&gt; &gt; different radios though. So many makes/models can work well.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I own the Paranormal Systems units and many of the Radio Shack hacks, and
&gt; &gt; by comparison, this little $20 model really holds it&#39;s own. PLUS it would be
&gt; &gt; handy in case of power outage. I think it&#39;s always great to have items
&gt; &gt; around the house that can fulfill more than one purpose. And so budget
&gt; &gt; friendly too. ;-)
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Just a thought.....
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Margaret
